rth Produced 'I-Land'|last=Otterson|first=Joe|work=Variety|date=September 28, 2018|access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref> On March 30, 2020, Netflix cancelled the series after one season.<ref name=\"Cancelled\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/netflix-cancels-v-wars-october-faction-after-one-season/|title=Netflix Cancels \u2018V-Wars\u2019 and \u2018October Faction\u2019 After 1 Season|last=Sippell|first=Margeaux|work=The Wrap|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nSometime after the series order announcement, it was confirmed that [[Tamara Taylor]], [[J.C. MacKenzie]], Aurora Burghart, Gabriel Darku, [[Wendy Crewson]], [[Megan Follows]] and [[Stephen McHattie]] would star in the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/october-faction-tamara-taylor-j-c-mackenzie-to-lead-cast-of-netflix-sci-fi-series-1202481702/|title='October Faction': Tamara Taylor & J.C. MacKenzie To Lead Cast Of Netflix Sci-Fi Series|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|date=12 October 2018|publisher=}}</ref> In October 2018, [[Maxim Roy]] was cast in a recurring role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/october-faction-maxim-roy-recur-netflix-sci-fi-series-1202483876/|title='October Faction': Maxim Roy To Recur In Netflix Sci-Fi Series|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|date=16 October 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming for the first season took place [[Location shooting|on location]] in [[Cambridge, Ontario|Cambridge]], [[Ontario]] from September to December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.therecord.com/news-story/8900125-new-netflix-series-films-in-cambridge/|title=New Netflix series films in Cambridge|last=Booth|first=Laura|work=The Record|date=September 13, 2018|access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n\nOn January 8, 2020, Netflix released the official trailer for the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/october-faction-netflix-first-trailer/|title=October Faction: Netflix's First Trailer Leans Into Horror (Excl)|last=Nolan|first=L.D.|work=[[Comic Book Resources]]|date=January 8, 2020|access-date=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n<!--AUDIENCE RECEPTION AND RATINGS: Do not include them! Wikipedia does not support user-generated content in its articles, and thus audience ratings cannot be included. Please refer to the talk page before proceeding to edit this section, and view the multiple discussions raised on the topic. No consensus has been formed to allow this article to differ from Wikipedia's guidelines and policies by including such content. Additions of audience ratings will be reverted.-->\n\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series holds an approval rating of 33% with an average rating of 5.5/10, based on 6 reviews.<!--The website's critical consensus states,--><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/october_faction/s01|title=October Faction: Season 1 (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Netflix title|80221644}}\n*{{IMDb title|8826128}}\n\n{{Netflix original ended series}}\n{{IDW Publishing}}\n\n[[Category:2020s American drama television series]]\n[[Category:2020 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2020s American horror television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American supernatural television series]]\n[[Category:American action television series]]\n[[Category:Dark fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:Dark fantasy web series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Science fiction horror web series]]\n[[Category:Serial drama television series]]\n[[Category:Suspense television series]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on comics]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Greater Sudbury]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Televi